"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The parameter 'norm_hist' is set to False while 'kde' is also set to False. According to the seaborn documentation, if 'kde' is False, the histogram should show counts rather than density. However, if a KDE or fitted density is plotted, 'norm_hist' should be set to True. Since 'kde' is False, the use of 'norm_hist' is not appropriate in this context.\",\n  \"patch\": \"5c5\\n< sns.distplot(data.tip, norm_hist=False, kde=False)\\n---\\n> sns.distplot(data.tip, norm_hist=False, kde=True)\"\n}"